# Feature Delivery Workflow

When **implementing** or **closing out** work tied to a Linear issue—especially
after **opening or updating a PR** or **handling review-bot feedback**—read and
follow the full playbook in:

`.cursor/skills/feature-workflow/SKILL.md`

That skill is authoritative for: verification command order, push/PR `gh`
usage, **5-minute waits** after PR creation and after each `@gemini review`,
fetching and resolving review threads, and **capping** automated re-review loops
with human escalation.

**Bot and inline suggestions** are not automatic edits: **critically analyze**
each proposed change before implementing (see
`.cursor/rules/pr-review-critical-analysis.mdc`).

Feature branches are expected in a **git worktree** (not only a branch switch in
the main checkout). Follow `.cursor/skills/git-worktrees/SKILL.md` for layout,
`make setup`, environment/ports, and cleanup.

Do not skip the waits when expecting Gemini Code Assist; poll only after the
wait. Default PR base branch for this repository is **`master`** unless the
default branch was renamed (confirm with `gh repo view`).
